Cell["\<\
This solution, like its immediate predecessor, seems to challenge our \
preconception for wave equation solutions. This solution also seems to behave \
like a mini wave with behavior towards the edges, but it also has heat \
equation behavior at the end of x domain. However, we can see enough of a \
similarity between the last two examples to infer a general shape for what \
wave and Poisson equation solutions might look like. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8587256002855253`*^9, 3.858725627939444*^9}, {
  3.8587256812927322`*^9, 
  3.8587258185183563`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c3441fe2-d488-4155-89a0-\
9a11d93efe11"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
3.) Discuss the method of eigenfunction expansion, the Helmholtz equation, \
and how it might be implemented for the solutions to nonhomogeneous heat and \
wave equations. \
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858262673916091*^9, 
  3.858262735368751*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"da998d22-28d7-454a-8ca8-\
df81557cc3f9"],

Cell["\<\
Much like the method of separation of variables, we can solve Partial \
Differential Equations using a certain technique for equally specific \
boundary conditions; enter the method of eigenfunction expansion.  Since we\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]re employing this technique for Laplace\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
equation, we\[CloseCurlyQuote]re solving the equation with particular \
boundary conditions to produce a result. 

The Helmholtz equation arises as a result of the time independent form of the \
wave equation and can be used in the context of Laplace\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
equation. Then, if we want to solve the nonhomogeneous heat and wave \
equations, we can use the Helmholtz equation as a starting point for the \
evaluation and solution. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858702398693756*^9, 3.858702424246414*^9}, {
  3.8587024704392433`*^9, 3.858702603081345*^9}, {3.858702695354986*^9, 
  3.858702726198388*^9}, {3.8587029199751472`*^9, 3.858702936685669*^9}, {
  3.858703037178808*^9, 3.85870304013892*^9}, {3.858703094556676*^9, 
  3.8587031241842117`*^9}, {3.858703237833891*^9, 
  3.8587032705538797`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aeda6c02-a370-4a9c-be7a-\
e006fba12890"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["3.10 Problems", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858262568599388*^9, 
  3.858262572104484*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3b3d7dba-6d30-431b-bfbb-\
554bbee3e904"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
2.) Plot all solutions to Poisson\[CloseCurlyQuote]s or Laplace\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s equation using the method of eigenfunction expansion for \
the given boundary conditions, and discuss the behavior of the solutions. \
Compare with solutions from section 3.9 (above). \
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8582627528948*^9, 
  3.8582628712849817`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a4ccfcd9-e2c7-491d-a908-\
d213e05e8489"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "a.) f(x,y) = 0, u(0,y) = u(\[Pi],y) = 0, u(x,0)=1, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["u", "y"], "(", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "733c998b-11ab-420f-a1ac-4b776809c120"],
 "."
}], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858277272294244*^9, 3.8582773584056168`*^9}, {
  3.858703311475506*^9, 3.8587033128885727`*^9}, {3.858703346004228*^9, 
  3.858703347907123*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"af5c42f9-2d74-4b36-8452-\
1afb6baa23dd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"u310a", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_"}], "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}], " ", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"4", "/", "Pi"}], " ", 
        RowBox[{"Cosh", "[", "y", "]"}]}], "+", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"1", "-", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"4", "/", "Pi"}], " ", 
             RowBox[{"Sinh", "[", "1", "]"}]}]}], ")"}], "/", 
          RowBox[{"Cosh", "[", "1", "]"}]}], ")"}], " ", 
        RowBox[{"Sinh", "[", "y", "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"Sum", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"n", "*", " ", "x"}], "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"2", "/", 
           RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"n", " ", "Pi"}], ")"}]}], 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"1", "-", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"(", 
              RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], "^", "n"}]}], ")"}], " ", 
          RowBox[{"Cosh", "[", 
           RowBox[{"n", " ", "*", "y"}], "]"}]}], "-", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"2", "/", 
           RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"n", " ", "Pi"}], ")"}]}], 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"1", "-", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"(", 
              RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], "^", "n"}]}], ")"}], 
          RowBox[{"Tanh", "[", "n", "]"}], 
          RowBox[{"Cosh", "[", 
           RowBox[{"n", " ", "*", "y"}], "]"}]}]}], ")"}]}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"n", ",", "2", ",", "20"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"Plot3D", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"u310a", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "y"}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "25"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"y", ",", "0", ",", "1"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"AxesLabel", "\[Rule]", "Automatic"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotLabel", "\[Rule]", "\"\<u310a\>\""}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858703358016947*^9, 3.8587037618927183`*^9}, {
   3.8587038410783997`*^9, 3.858703846543725*^9}, {3.8587040874103727`*^9, 
   3.8587041317599077`*^9}, {3.8587042072220173`*^9, 3.85870421454254*^9}, {
   3.858704306151876*^9, 3.85870444699955*^9}, {3.8587048845993757`*^9, 
   3.8587049137739964`*^9}, 3.858705069598027*^9, {3.858705208932952*^9, 
   3.8587052314878807`*^9}, {3.858705269183823*^9, 3.858705277593927*^9}, 
   3.858720093690196*^9, {3.858720351467929*^9, 3.858720358823544*^9}, {
   3.8587258558865643`*^9, 3.85872587299024*^9}, {3.858726180147943*^9, 
   3.85872618070968*^9}},
